column919:
06/Sep/2022 08:11 AM;6116765;Hi [~Ashok.Jha]
We don't include the accredited _hours_ in the Metadata or Catalogue, as the 'Duration' listed on the IBF Accredited PDF typically reflects the duration of the course i.e. in this instance, 60 minutes (1 hour). 

In terms of completing the 'Accredited' field, it would need populating with "IBF Accredited", no duration required. 

I hope this helps.

;;;
column920:
07/Sep/2022 05:19 AM;6031505;Hi,

All this while we have updating the field for accredited courses.

!image-2022-09-07-10-49-09-865.png!

 

In a discussion with Madhur, we understood, value in this field was derived from course duration. (Eg: For a 30 min course, field value will be 0.5; while for a 60 min course, it will be 1). However, I am not sure it is documented anywhere. To my knowledge, this was a part of the rollout email shared by Madhur.

column1: Numotion - issues with PDH courses via the Profiler
column25:
Please see attached two emails from the client, detailing the client's issues - also copying below for ease:
* Course glitches and stops during session.
* Does not save at current stopping point, returns student back to the beginning when they go back to the course.
* Does not issue certificate upon receiving 100% on test.
* Does not reflect progress if started so we cannot see where they stopped or timed out.
* SCORM file(s) are not supporting pausing or saving the learner’s place.
* Multiple errors popping in the course which took one of their VPs 2 hours to complete and still shows as “in progress” on my dashboard (applies to the Managers and Employees version)
* Another VP spent over 3 hours completing the harassment training. The learner had to click through several error messages to advance each screen throughout the entire training. The learner completed and passed the assessment then closed out of the training however it is still showing “in progress” and when the learner re-enters the training to pick up where I left off it is at slide 16 of 134.


*Please note:* the client has not specified which PDH courses these issues relate to, only that it relates to PDH via the Profiler.

Attached is their SOW which lists all the PDHs that could be applicable - also copying below for ease:

Preventing Discrimination and Harassment for Employees (US) 00313_WC_R1_eng_v12.2
Preventing Discrimination and Harassment for Managers (US) 00314_WC_R1_eng_v12
Preventing Discrimination and Harassment for Employees (California) 00671_WC_R1_eng_v2.2
Preventing Discrimination and Harassment for Managers (California) 00312_WC_R1_eng_v12.2
Preventing Discrimination and Harassment for Employees and Supervisors (Connecticut) 
00687_WC_RA_eng_v2
Preventing Discrimination and Harassment for Managers (Connecticut) 00407_WC_R1_eng_v12.1
Preventing Discrimination and Harassment for Employees (Maine) 00411_WC_R1_eng_v12
Preventing Discrimination and Harassment for Managers (Maine) 00412_WC_R1_eng_v12
Preventing Discrimination and Harassment for Employees (NY) 00666_WC_R1_eng_v3
Preventing Discrimination and Harassment for Managers (NY) 00665_WC_R1_eng_v3

Note: client LMS is Greenlight.

column1: Sentinel One - PDH US Fundamentals - client faced difficulty in progressing after the last chapter
column25:
For context, as this may help: 
We are due to update the fixed timing version of this PDH US Fundamentals course by 30th September, however this would be too long to ask the client to wait for an updated version. All details below.

Please see attached the client email's - please refer to the first paragraph. Image is within the email attachment,

Copying the feedback below for ease too:
On the first module of the employee training, under the Preventing Discrimination and Harassment US Fundamentals, client found it difficult to progress after the last chapter. 

The client clicked on the following: 
* each of the people to review the role of the person in the situation;
* the "contacting state agencies" link; and 
* on one of the states.

However, after doing all of that, the Next arrow did not activate, so the client was unable to progress. 

Please would you investigate.

column908:
31/Aug/2022 10:57 AM;6035810;Hi [~Ashok.Jha]

I seem to recall we looked into this issue recently. I believe Ali reported it whilst testing the course for a client.

What was happening is there is a 120 second (2 min) timer on that page. 

This timer starts when the user lands on the page but it seems that users are completing all necessary interactions in that page well within the 2 minute timer. So with a lack of visual indication they are waiting a very long time before the next button appears. 

I've copied over the latest version of the fixed duration course and previewed this and after a long wait, I can confirm the next button does appear after a long wait.

So this is not a bug with the course as such but it's not great user experience. As it's been flagged up a number of times now we ought to look into how to update this to improve the user experience. From my experience the timer does seem excessive on this page. Screenshots below of enabled next button after waiting on the page for timer to run it's course. 

I recall Anthony will soon be working on updates on the Fundamentals course and I think that might address this issue. So probably not one we need to action immediately at this moment in time?

!image-2022-08-31-11-54-07-159.png|width=631,height=355!

!image-2022-08-31-11-54-27-779.png|width=630,height=354!

CC [~Ashok.Jha];;;

Attached .mp4 file above.

CC [~Ashok.Jha];;;

Best

column1: MAZARS USA_Data Privacy and Security & GDPR
column25:
Sarah Chow of Mazars USA is asking as to why the certificates she have for her two courses, "Data Privacy and Security" and "GDPR" do not have the option to "Print" compared her certificate the HIPAA course. Mazars USA is using its own LMS and the interface is different from the standard CLMS page of Thomson Reuters.

To further illustrate her concern, I have attached the photos of her certificates. The "Print" option that she is referring to is encircled in her HIPAA certificate.

 

!image-2022-08-25-22-00-48-320.png|width=1502,height=826!

!image-2022-08-25-22-05-16-009.png|width=1503,height=1015!

26/Aug/2022 06:39 AM;6031259;Hi [~Ashok.Jha]

All three courses have different framework, the HIPPA course title built on the earlier version of the framework where we used to add that print button feature, in other two courses are developed in the newer version of the framework where this print feature was removed. 

Depending on the framework used features may very in the respective courses.

Best
Arpit;;;

The user is using their own LMS platform which is quite different from the standard Thomson Reuters interface.

Thank you so much for your support.;;;
column909:
30/Aug/2022 04:31 AM;6031259;Hi [~Ashok.Jha]

if the client LMS have the same feature like our LMS have to integrate the certificate on LMS level after completion the course. this

Best
Arpit;;;

Thank you for attending to each of my questions and for your support.

May I know what do you mean with this?

"if the client LMS have the same feature like our LMS have to integrate the certificate on LMS level after completion the course"

The client would like to have the "Download your Certificate" option in their LMS (similar to our LMS) and they are using Adobe Learning Manager.

Is this something we can help them with?

Thank you.;;;
column913:
01/Sep/2022 03:05 AM;6031259;Hi [~Ashok.Jha]

Every LMS have some different kind of setup, if the client LMS have the option where they configuring/uploading the course to issue/add the certificate.

so they need to check with their LMS administrator on this if there is any feature available while uploading the course in settings from they can add the certificate, in this case if certificate option is there as soon as learner will pass the training LMS will automatically issue the certificate for the respective learner. 

Please ask them to check with their LMS team.

Best

column1: Triumvirate Environmental_Preventing sexual harassment for California employees
column25:
Please see client's email below.

 

I received a comment regarding one of the Preventing Harassment and Discrimination trainings, which does not seem to be related to the size of the frame, but actually related to the items on the screen. I believe he is saying that the text is being cut off. See screenshots below.

 

Receiving another complaint from someone taking the California Employees edition (non managers) and they are unable to move forward after the video was completed. Comments below and screenshots from the user attached.

 

The user states:
 “I am trying to complete the Training: Preventing Discrimination and Harassment/CA Employees version. I get to the section "Did he come in today" and there are four blocks. When I complete the third, the video will not allow me to advance, and I continually start back at the beginning again. I have answered the questions correctly, but the advance button does not authorize me to move forward.”

 

“Yes, I finish the video and the button to advance does not populate. It stays "grayed out" and I just start the video again. I have watched several times, answered the questions correctly, and it still cycles back to the beginning. I also use Google Chrome.”

 

We are receiving many more complaints regarding the same issue. These are all for the California employees edition.

 

[~6031259] 
[~6022069]

Prosearch sent an email to Sarah I on 15/08 with the following feedback after the incremental updates were made to PDH California Employee Edition and Manager Edition packages:

'[Client] was able to successfully complete the California employee course without incident. The user experience was as expected with no delays. However, the US Fundamentals course continues to be problematic. I know you note that the team there did multiple rounds of QA without incident, but we are experiencing otherwise.

[The client] has shared some screenshots of the first 3 chapters where advancement timing delays seem excessive. On the attached, please look at the first and last example in particular as those two are similar in that the questions appear during the video and display the success message but do not allow advancement for multiple minutes, even after displaying the message that you completed the quiz successfully.

[The client has] also had our HR team take the course and they too had the same experience with delays and were confused by having completed the quiz/video but not being able to advance. I asked them to try again while I watched, and they too experienced the multiple minute delay and viewed the delay as problematic.'

Client tested on Windows 10, Chrome.

Unsure of number of impacted users for Prosearch as the files were sent for client LMS on this occasion.

Please see attached email for client and Sarah I contact details.

MR folder is T:\Z - DESIGN FOLDER\COURSES\Market Ready\2021\Preventing_Discrimination_and_Harassment_Modules_(US)_8705

column1: ICIMS INC_Preventing Discrimination and Harassment For Employees and Managers Canada Edition
column25:
Hello, Team. One of our clients who is using their own LMS reached out to us due to the issue encountered with the Preventing Discrimination and Harassment For Employees and Managers Canada Edition courses. They're requesting for  updated zip files for this training. Please see details below and attached are the screenshots of the errors for reference.
 # *00426_WC_RA_eng_v13 Preventing Discrimination and Harassment for Employees: Canada Edition – icims_pdh_canada_eng_v1_2004*
 # *00315_WC_RA_eng_v13 Preventing Discrimination and Harassment for Managers: Canada Edition – icims_pdh_mgr_can_eng_v1_2004*

_A few employees both manager and employee levels made me aware that the pictured screen does not let them pass even though they’ve clicked “Closed Window” multiple times. I’ve logged in as each effected team member and replicated the issue myself as well as re-versioned the course in cornerstone and was still able to replicate both issues. I went as far as clearing my cache and assigning the training to myself as well and to no avail was I able to complete the training either._

Can you kindly assist on this and reach out to the client? Below is the client's contact information:

Mackenzie Egan

[Mackenzie.Egan@icims.com|mailto:Mackenzie.Egan@icims.com]

ICIMS Inc

Please let me know if you need anything else.

Regards,

Dani Alea

18/Aug/2022 03:31 PM;6035810;Hi [~Ashok.Jha]

Unusual problem, hard to tell what's the issue but it appears there is overlapping text, so I think something is causing the course to not load fully or something is interfering with the actions and scripts in the course.

In any case I've looked into the courses and couldn't identify anything that's clearly creating the problem.

So I've repackaged the courses as SCORM 2004 courses as per our internal process for uploading to CLMS (without post publish files). I've tested them in CLMS as well from start to finish and they appear to function properly. I believe these packages should work fine on Cornerstone.

The packages can be downloaded from below:

[https://elearningcompliance.thomsonreuters.com/File_Hosting/ICIMS/icims_pdh_canada_eng_v1_SCORM_2004_20220818.zip]

[https://elearningcompliance.thomsonreuters.com/File_Hosting/ICIMS/icims_pdh_mgr_can_eng_v1_SCORM_2004_20220818.zip]

Please let us know what client reports back with, thank you.

CC [~Ashok.Jha]

 

 ;;;

column907:
16/Aug/2022 01:22 PM;6035810;Hi [~Ashok.Jha]

I think most of the points is course level behaviour. However I think one can be fixed. Looping [~Ashok.Jha] for any additional comments. Mine are below.
 # The last attempt is counted when calculating security rating. For Eg: if user attempts the question incorrect and then correct in the second attempt. the correct attempt will be considered while calculating the security rating. 
*KC - looking the actions for the question pages it looks like it's setup to behave in such a manner. So your score can change with each reattempt.*
 # As soon as we enter a chapter and go back to Menu, Security rating for that chapter changes to 'Very Weak security'. Ideally, rating should display only after the chapter is complete
*KC - when you enter a chapter there is an action group that does a full reset of the questions within a chapter. I believe this is needed for the scoring to work, I expect this is template level behaviour from the original Info Sec course.* 
 # Complete a chapter and a security rating appears. Now revisit the chapter and reattempt the questions. Security rating changes. However highlighting for the bars does not change. As seen in the screenshot, three bars are highlighted orange, while security rating is "very poor security" 
*KC - For the example above I think I know the reason why. There were +2 questions+ that were setting the score for the +chapter 1 question 1 variable.+* So even if you get them all right for that chapter it will only set to 3/4 max. I'll update it for chapter 1 and have a look at the rest of the course.;;;

column914:
23/Aug/2022 11:46 AM;6070444;Steps:
1. Condition 1: Learner attempts 0 or less than 4 questions per chapter - security rating will not be displayed, it will show gray lines
2. Condition 2: Learner attempts all 4 questions but not all pages in a chapter: security rating will be displayed
3. Condition 3: Learner attempts all 4 questions and all pages in a chapter:  security rating will be displayed

Scoring:
0/4 -> Very Weak Security
1/4->Weak Security
2/4->Moderate Security
3/4-> Strong Security
4/4-> Very Strong Security;;;
column915:
25/Aug/2022 05:50 AM;6070444;Hello [~Ashok.Jha] [~Ashok.Jha] [~Ashok.Jha] [~Ashok.Jha]
Final outcome:
IT Security Meter

Steps:

1. Condition 1: Learner attempts 0 or less than 4 questions per chapter - security rating will not be displayed, it will show gray lines

2. Condition 2: Learner attempts all 4 questions but not all pages in a chapter: security rating will be displayed

3. Condition 3: Learner attempts all 4 questions and all pages in a chapter:  security rating will be displayed



Scoring:

0/4 -> Very Weak Security

1/4->Weak Security

2/4->Moderate Security

3/4-> Strong Security

4/4-> Very Strong Security

The CYU quiz questions in every chapter, once attempted, will be frozen, once attempted;;;

Peng Ling Tan (tanpengling@lionglobalinvestors.com)

column25:
Pre-assessment scoring not captured on CLMS.

This issue was raised internally during the creation of the German version of this course, after the English was signed off.

Please see https://jira.thomsonreuters.com/browse/TCL-29171 for details on fix.

Ajay confirmed on the other ticket that he looked at [German] source and functionality is set to only send score from pre assessment if score is higher than 90%. The same functionality is available in English version also. However for other deliveries to abrdn there is no such condition for pre-assessment score.

There was no specific request from the client for the scoring of this assessment to work any differently to other abrdn courses - there is just a requirement for a mandatory Q7.

Anthony confirmed for the German course abrdn checklist was not followed - [abrdn Course Delivery|https://trten.sharepoint.com/:f:/s/GlobalComplianceLearningOperations/EuqtNjyrjzBMiLzieel05n8BZVKhv5qZSW5RhEH5uvVPTA]

Pre assessment results page had the wrong look and feel. It had the chart circle score which caused issues.

Issue reported on Windows 10, Chrome by TR QA (Ali).

4109 impacted users on Live course. We need to retain existing users completion records.

This needs updating on CLMS and an updated SCORM package for client LMS creating please.

!image-2022-07-26-03-51-49-153.png!

It seems like the issue is from prerequisites setting of the course.

> [~6022069]
